history.content:
@Michael-David Sasson  @Cindy Conners  @Lydia Raya  

For the CS classes, enrolling during phase 1 will not increase your chances.  I can't promise it will work out in phase 2 but that is when we can look at it more closely.

I'm currently an Engineering Physics major, but I'm probably going to switch to EECS by the end of this semester. Since I won't have priority enrollment for CS classes when my phase 1 begins (end April, I wouldn't have switched majors yet), how likely is it that I get into EE126, EE16B, CS 70 and CS 184 in phase 2? Should enroll in these classes in phase 1 and get placed on the waitlist, or will I be fine enrolling in phase 2?
